Script to retrieve a file, including file checks and aborts as needed. .ZIP files are automatically extracted. ComputerFilePath = Path and filename to save the downloaded file LTFilePath = Path to file in LTShare, or URL to file download. See Supported Examples below. LTFilePath now accepts multiple sources, separated by "|". Optional Variables: ComputerFileForced = 1: Forces file to be redownloaded bypassing cache ComputerFileForced = 0 (or missing): File will be downloaded from cache, file download will be skipped if file already exists LTFileMD5Hash: If defined, file will be rejected if the MD5 hash does not match. LTFileMD5Hash = GENERATE - Only for LTShare downloads, calculates MD5 checksum on server ComputerFileSizeMinBytes = X>0: Sets the minimum accepted size for the downloaded file. If the file is smaller it is assumed corrupt/incomplete. ComputerFileSizeMaxBytes = X>0: Sets the maximum accepted size for the downloaded file. If the file is larger it is assumed corrupt or modified. ComputerFilePreserve = 1: Do not perform post download processing (unzip, etc.) ComputerFilePreserve = 0 (or missing): Attempt to extract or prepare compressed archive. Modifies ComputerFilePath value to be the folder path of the extracted files. VERBOSE > 0 - Enables additional script logging VERBOSE <= 0 (Default) - Normal script output ComputerFileDownloadLimit = X > 0 - Number of download attempts allowed per source.
Return Variables: ComputerFilePath = "ERROR" if the file could not be downloaded. ComputerFilePath = The path to the downloaded file ComputerFilePath = The path to the folder where the downloaded file was extracted if ComputerFilePreserve<>1
Examples: LTShare: LTFilePath=Utilities\filenamehere.exe HTTP: LTFilePath=http://www.download.com/myfile/filenamehere.exe HTTPS: LTFilePath=https://www.download.com/myfile/filenamehere.exe UNC Path: LTFilePath=\\localserver\sharename\folder\filenamehere.exe SFTP: LTFilePath=sftp://<USERNAME>:<PASS>@<SFTPHOST>/<FOLDERANDFILE>|<SFTP HOSTKEY STRING> Example: LTFilePath=sftp://fakeuser:fakepass@myserver/folder/filenamehere.exe|ssh-rsa 1024 ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
